n center. But these services may more closely resemble the phenomenon of wraparound incarceration, in which students, despite leaving the actual detention center, cannot escape the surveillance of formal detention, and are thereby slowly pushed away from traditional schooling and a productive life course.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aFemale juvenile delinquentsxCalifornia, Southern. 0aFemale juvenile delinquentszCalifornia, SouthernvCase studies. 0aFemale juvenile delinquentszCalifornia, Southern. 0aHispanic American teenage girlsxEducation (Secondary)xCalifornia, Southern. 0aHispanic American teenage girlsxEducation (Secondary)zCalifornia, SouthernvCase studies. 0aHispanic American teenage girlsxEducation (Secondary)zCalifornia, Southern. 0aHispanic American teenage girlsxSocial conditionsxCalifornia, Southern. 0aHispanic American teenage girlszCalifornia, SouthernxSocial conditionsvCase studies. 0aHispanic American teenage girlszCalifornia, SouthernxSocial conditions. 0aJuvenile detention homesxCalifornia, Southern. 0aJuvenile detention homeszCalifornia, SouthernvCase studies. 0aJuvenile detention homeszCalifornia, Southern. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  aamerican justice system.  acalifornia schools.  acalifornia.  achildrens studies.  acrime.  ael valle juvenile detention center.  aformal detention.  agender and justice series.  agender studies.  ahispanic american studies.  aincarceration.  ainstitutions of confinement.  ajuvenile detention.  alatina girls.  alatina.  alegacy community school.  alegislation.  alos angeles.  amass incarceration.  aprison.  aschool to prison pipeline.  aschool.  asocial science.  asurveillance.  aunited states of america.  awomen and girls.  awraparound incarceration.  